{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875184417,"sessionID":"ses_285995f58ffe7A06Rb3mqAo6n0","part":{"id":"prt_d7a66b1b6001zK2Bw47NPaRx6k","messageID":"msg_d7a66a1a70012WRHCWwvmzIchS","sessionID":"ses_285995f58ffe7A06Rb3mqAo6n0","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_3d2378cd44324ff686c1c1a3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project at /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall project structure (top-level directories and key files)\n2. Any existing spec files (look for *.md files with \"spec\" in the name, delta-spec.md, or similar)\n3. Any existing Dockerfile or docker-related files\n4. Any OpenSpec format examples in the project\n5. The project's purpose and what \"agentcube\" does\n\nSearch thoroughly - check for patterns like **/*spec*.md, **/delta-spec.md, **/Dockerfile*, **/openspec*, **/specs/**, etc.\n\nReturn:\n- Project structure overview\n- Any existing spec file paths and their format conventions\n- Any Dockerfile paths found\n- Key information about what the project does","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_28599347dffe5Yb3OinHAECAXO (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a thorough understanding of the project. Here is the complete report:\n\n---\n\n## AgentCube Project Exploration Report\n\n### 1. Project Structure Overview\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/\n```\n\n**Top-level directories and key files:**\n\n| Path | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `cmd/` | Go binaries: `agentd/`, `cli/`, `picod/`, `router/`, `workloadmanager/` |\n| `pkg/` | Go packages: `agentd/`, `apis/`, `common/`, `picod/`, `router/`, `store/`, `workloadmanager/` |\n| `changes/` | 32 change request directories (AR-001 through AR-032), each with `delta-spec.md`, `design.md`, `proposal.md`, `tasks.md` |\n| `manifests/` | Helm charts (`charts/`) |\n| `ci-cd/` | CI/CD spec |\n| `cli-toolkit/` | CLI spec |\n| `code-execution/` | Code execution spec |\n| `deployment/` | Deployment spec |\n| `idle-cleanup/` | Idle cleanup spec |\n| `integrations/` | Integrations spec (Dify plugin, PCAP analyzer) |\n| `python-sdk/` | Python SDK spec |\n| `sandbox-orchestration/` | Sandbox orchestration spec |\n| `session-routing/` | Session routing spec |\n| `session-store/` | Session store spec |\n| `agentd/` | Agent daemon |\n| `client-go/` | Go client |\n| `test/`, `testing/` | Test infrastructure |\n| `go.mod` | Go module: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`, Go 1.25.0 |\n| `go.sum` | Go dependency lockfile |\n| `project.md` | OpenSpec project context document |\n| `design.md` | Detailed design document (AR-029, 792 lines) |\n| `proposal.md` | Change proposal (AR-028, 319 lines) |\n| `tasks.md` | Task breakdown (AR-023, 185 lines) |\n| `delta-spec.md` | Root delta spec (AR-029, 366 lines) |\n| `test_spec.md` | Test spec |\n| `.sdd_prompt.md` | SDD prompt for AI-assisted design generation |\n| `coverage.out`, `.coverage`, `.pytest_cache/` | Test coverage artifacts |\n\n---\n\n### 2. Spec Files Found\n\n**Total: 36 spec-related `.md` files**\n\n#### A. Root-level spec files:\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md` -- AR-029 delta spec (366 lines)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/test_spec.md`\n\n#### B. Subdirectory base specs (`{module}/spec.md`):\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cli-toolkit/spec.md` (197 lines)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/code-execution/spec.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/ci-cd/spec.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/deployment/spec.md` (96 lines)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/idle-cleanup/spec.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/integrations/spec.md` (191 lines)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/python-sdk/spec.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md` (176 lines)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/session-routing/spec.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/session-store/spec.md`\n\n#### C. Change request delta specs (`changes/AR-XXX/delta-spec.md`):\n25 delta specs found, from AR-002 through AR-032 (with gaps at AR-001, AR-008, AR-009, AR-012-AR-016). Examples:\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-002/delta-spec.md` (177 lines)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md` (22 lines, mostly TODOs)\n\n---\n\n### 3. Spec Format Conventions\n\nThe project uses a formal **OpenSpec** format with two spec types:\n\n**Base Specs** (`{module}/spec.md`):\n- Title: `# {Module Name} Specification`\n- Section: `## Purpose` -- brief description\n- Section: `## Requirements` -- each requirement follows this pattern:\n  ```\n  ### Requirement: {Requirement Name}\n  The system SHALL/SHOULD/MAY {normative statement}.\n\n  #### Scenario: {Scenario Name}\n  - **GIVEN** {precondition}\n  - **WHEN** {action}\n  - **THEN** {expected outcome}\n  ```\n\n**Delta Specs** (`changes/AR-XXX/delta-spec.md`):\n- Title: `# AR-XXX: {Title} -- Delta Spec`\n- Section: `## Context` -- Module, Language, Size, Base specs references\n- Section: `## Scope` or `## Delta Requirements`\n- Requirements use the same GIVEN/WHEN/THEN BDD-style scenario format\n- Some include `## File Changes` tables\n\n**Normative language**: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional.\n\nEach change request directory (`changes/AR-XXX/`) contains four files:\n- `proposal.md` -- purpose, scope, impact analysis, alternatives, acceptance criteria\n- `design.md` -- architecture, data structures, API contracts, error handling, testing strategy\n- `delta-spec.md` -- delta requirements in GIVEN/WHEN/THEN format\n- `tasks.md` -- task breakdown with dependency graphs and parallelizable groups\n\n---\n\n### 4. Dockerfile / Docker-Related Files\n\n**No Dockerfiles currently exist in the repository.** The `docker/` directory referenced in the deployment spec (`deployment/spec.md`, line 78) does not exist yet. The deployment spec describes three Dockerfiles that *should* be created:\n- `docker/Dockerfile` -- Workload Manager\n- `docker/Dockerfile.router` -- Router\n- `docker/Dockerfile.picod` -- picod daemon\n\nAR-032 (`changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md`) is titled \"Dockerfile multi-stage build (3 images)\" but its content is mostly TODO placeholders, indicating this work is planned but not yet implemented.\n\nNo `docker-compose` files or `.dockerignore` files were found either.\n\n---\n\n### 5. What AgentCube Does\n\n**AgentCube** is a **Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents**. It is developed under the Volcano project (`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`).\n\n**Core capabilities:**\n\n1. **Sandbox Provisioning** -- Creates isolated sandbox pods on demand via Kubernetes CRDs (`AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` in API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`)\n\n2. **Session-Aware Traffic Routing** -- Routes HTTP traffic to sandbox pods through proxies, using session IDs (`x-agentcube-session-id` header)\n\n3. **Lifecycle Management** -- Manages sandbox creation, expiry, and idle cleanup (via `agentd` daemon)\n\n4. **Code Execution** -- Provides a Code Interpreter API for executing arbitrary code/commands in isolated sandboxes\n\n5. **Agent Runtime** -- Provides an Agent Runtime API for invoking AI agents deployed as Kubernetes workloads\n\n**Architecture components:**\n- **Workload Manager** (Go/Gin) -- Control plane API for creating/deleting sandboxes\n- **Router** (Go/Gin) -- Data plane proxy that routes session traffic to sandbox pods\n- **PicoD** -- Optional daemon running inside sandbox pods\n- **Agentd** -- Idle cleanup controller\n- **Python SDK** (`agentcube`) -- Client library with `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient`\n- **CLI** (`kubectl-agentcube`) -- Typer-based CLI for packaging, building, publishing, and invoking agents\n- **Redis/Valkey** -- Session store for sandbox state persistence\n- **Helm chart** -- Deployment packaging\n\n**Tech stack:** Go 1.24/1.25 (server), Python 3.10+ (CLI/SDK), Gin (Go HTTP), Kubernetes CRDs + controller-runtime, Redis/Valkey, JWT RS256 auth, Helm 3, Docusaurus (docs).\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_28599347dffe5Yb3OinHAECAXO","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project","time":{"start":1775875050368,"end":1775875184414}}}}
