{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875201673,"sessionID":"ses_285995f58ffe7A06Rb3mqAo6n0","part":{"id":"prt_d7a69155c001WPi5dnIT2pF9Rn","messageID":"msg_d7a690b07001zCO76DVAQWSq2I","sessionID":"ses_285995f58ffe7A06Rb3mqAo6n0","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_cc34cb42514a4587a7a3fefc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-002/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-002/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-002: CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the Go type system for the `CodeInterpreter` Custom Resource Definition in API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, enabling declarative management of code execution sandbox environments with warm pool support and authentication mode configuration.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter CRD type definition\n10: \n11: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreter` as a namespaced Kubernetes custom resource with `Spec` and `Status` subfields, registered in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group.\n12: \n13: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter type is a valid Kubernetes object\n14: - **GIVEN** the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` file exists\n15: - **WHEN** the Go compiler processes the package\n16: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreter` SHALL embed `metav1.TypeMeta` and `metav1.ObjectMeta`, and implement `runtime.Object` via `+k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object`\n17: \n18: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter has status subresource enabled\n19: - **GIVEN** the `+kubebuilder:subresource:status` marker is present on the `CodeInterpreter` type\n20: - **WHEN** `controller-gen crd` generates the CRD YAML\n21: - **THEN** the resulting CRD SHALL include `/status` as a subresource endpoint\n22: \n23: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter is namespaced\n24: - **GIVEN** the `+kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced` marker is present\n25: - **WHEN** the CRD is applied to a cluster\n26: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreter` resources SHALL be scoped to a namespace and require namespace qualification in API requests\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter displays Age column in kubectl output\n29: - **GIVEN** the `+kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"` marker is present\n30: - **WHEN** a user runs `kubectl get codeinterpreters`\n31: - **THEN** the output SHALL include an `AGE` column derived from `.metadata.creationTimestamp`\n32: \n33: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterSpec fields\n34: \n35: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterSpec` with fields for port configuration (`Ports`), sandbox template (`Template`), session timeouts (`SessionTimeout`, `MaxSessionDuration`), warm pool sizing (`WarmPoolSize`), and authentication mode (`AuthMode`).\n36: \n37: #### Scenario: Spec uses shared TargetPort type for ports\n38: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterSpec` with `Ports` field\n39: - **WHEN** the type is serialized to JSON\n40: - **THEN** the JSON key SHALL be `ports` (not `targetPort`), and each entry SHALL conform to the shared `TargetPort` struct with `pathPrefix`, `name`, `port`, and `protocol` fields\n41: \n42: #### Scenario: Template uses flat CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate\n43: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterSpec` with `Template` field\n44: - **WHEN** the template is inspected\n45: - **THEN** it SHALL be of type `*CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate` with flat fields (`image`, `command`, `args`, `resources`, `environment`, `labels`, `annotations`, `runtimeClassName`, `imagePullPolicy`, `imagePullSecrets`) and SHALL NOT embed `corev1.PodSpec`\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: WarmPoolSize is optional\n48: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterSpec` with `WarmPoolSize` set to `nil`\n49: - **WHEN** the spec is serialized to JSON\n50: - **THEN** the `warmPoolSize` field SHALL be omitted from the output (omitempty behavior)\n51: \n52: #### Scenario: AuthMode defaults to empty string\n53: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterSpec` with `AuthMode` not explicitly set\n54: - **WHEN** the spec is inspected\n55: - **THEN** `AuthMode` SHALL equal `AuthModeType(\"\")` (empty string), not any specific enum value\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: SessionTimeout and MaxSessionDuration use metav1.Duration\n58: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterSpec` with `SessionTimeout` set to 15 minutes\n59: - **WHEN** the spec is serialized to JSON\n60: - **THEN** `sessionTimeout` SHALL render as a duration string (e.g., `\"15m0s\"`) per `metav1.Duration` marshaling\n61: \n62: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterStatus fields\n63: \n64: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterStatus` with `Conditions` (standard Kubernetes condition slice) and `Ready` (boolean readiness indicator).\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Status includes standard conditions\n67: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterStatus` with conditions\n68: - **WHEN** the status is serialized to JSON\n69: - **THEN** `conditions` SHALL be an array of `metav1.Condition` objects with `type`, `status`, `reason`, `message`, and `lastTransitionTime` fields\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Ready field indicates operational state\n72: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterStatus` with `Ready: true`\n73: - **WHEN** the status is inspected via client-go\n74: - **THEN** `status.ready` SHALL return `true`, indicating the CodeInterpreter is operational\n75: \n76: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate fields\n77: \n78: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate` with flat configuration fields for sandbox pod creation, including image, pull policy, secrets, environment variables, command, arguments, resource requirements, labels, annotations, and runtime class.\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Template supports custom labels and annotations\n81: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate` with `Labels: {\"app\": \"code-interpreter\"}` and `Annotations: {\"agentcube.io/version\": \"1\"}`\n82: - **WHEN** the template is applied to a sandbox pod\n83: - **THEN** the resulting pod SHALL have those labels and annotations propagated\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: Template supports resource requirements\n86: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate` with `Resources` set to `corev1.ResourceRequirements{Requests: {\"cpu\": \"1\", \"memory\": \"2Gi\"}}`\n87: - **WHEN** the template is serialized to JSON\n88: - **THEN** `resources` SHALL include `requests` with `cpu` and `memory` values per Kubernetes resource quantity format\n89: \n90: #### Scenario: Template supports runtimeClassName\n91: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate` with `RuntimeClassName` set to `\"kuasar-vmm\"`\n92: - **WHEN** the template is serialized to JSON\n93: - **THEN** `runtimeClassName` SHALL be `\"kuasar-vmm\"` in the output\n94: \n95: ### Requirement: AuthModeType and ProtocolType enumerations\n96: \n97: The system SHALL define `AuthModeType` with values `picod` and `none`, and `ProtocolType` with values `HTTP` and `HTTPS`, as typed string constants.\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: AuthModeType constants are valid\n100: - **GIVEN** the constants `AuthModePicoD` and `AuthModeNone` are defined\n101: - **WHEN** their values are inspected\n102: - **THEN** `AuthModePicoD` SHALL equal `\"picod\"` and `AuthModeNone` SHALL equal `\"none\"`\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: ProtocolType constants are valid\n105: - **GIVEN** the constants `ProtocolTypeHTTP` and `ProtocolTypeHTTPS` are defined\n106: - **WHEN** their values are inspected\n107: - **THEN** `ProtocolTypeHTTP` SHALL equal `\"HTTP\"` and `ProtocolTypeHTTPS` SHALL equal `\"HTTPS\"`\n108: \n109: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterList type\n110: \n111: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterList` as a Kubernetes list type containing a slice of `CodeInterpreter` items, registered with the scheme.\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterList implements runtime.Object\n114: - **GIVEN** the `+k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object` marker on `CodeInterpreterList`\n115: - **WHEN** the list is passed to a Kubernetes client\n116: - **THEN** it SHALL be accepted as a valid `runtime.Object` for list operations\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: List items are accessible\n119: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterList` with two items\n120: - **WHEN** the `Items` field is iterated\n121: - **THEN** each item SHALL be a `CodeInterpreter` with fully populated `Spec` and `Status`\n122: \n123: ### Requirement: Scheme registration\n124: \n125: The system SHALL register `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` kinds and their GroupVersionKind constants in `register.go` using the shared `SchemeBuilder`.\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: Kind constants are defined\n128: - **GIVEN** the `register.go` file\n129: - **WHEN** the constants are inspected\n130: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreterKind` SHALL equal `\"CodeInterpreter\"`, `CodeInterpreterListKind` SHALL equal `\"CodeInterpreterList\"`, and `CodeInterpreterGroupVersionKind` SHALL equal `GroupVersion.WithKind(\"CodeInterpreter\")`\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: Types are registered with the scheme\n133: - **GIVEN** the `init()` function in `codeinterpreter_types.go` calls `SchemeBuilder.Register(&CodeInterpreter{}, &CodeInterpreterList{})`\n134: - **WHEN** the package is imported\n135: - **THEN** both types SHALL be registered in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` scheme\n136: \n137: ### Requirement: Shared type reuse\n138: \n139: The system SHALL reuse `TargetPort`, `ProtocolType`, and `AuthModeType` types defined in the same package (shared with AR-001 AgentRuntime) to avoid duplication.\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter and AgentRuntime share TargetPort\n142: - **GIVEN** both `agent_type.go` and `codeinterpreter_types.go` reference `TargetPort`\n143: - **WHEN** the package is compiled\n144: - **THEN** there SHALL be exactly one definition of `TargetPort` in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` used by both CRD types\n145: \n146: ### Requirement: DeepCopy generation\n147: \n148: The system SHALL generate `DeepCopy`, `DeepCopyInto`, and `DeepCopyObject` methods for all CodeInterpreter types via `controller-gen object`.\n149: \n150: #### Scenario: DeepCopy methods exist for CodeInterpreter\n151: - **GIVEN** `make generate` has been run\n152: - **WHEN** `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` is inspected\n153: - **THEN** it SHALL contain `DeepCopyInto` and `DeepCopy` methods for `CodeInterpreter`, `CodeInterpreterSpec`, `CodeInterpreterStatus`, `CodeInterpreterList`, and `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`\n154: \n155: #### Scenario: DeepCopy produces independent copies\n156: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with nested `Template.Labels` map\n157: - **WHEN** `DeepCopy()` is called and the copy's labels are modified\n158: - **THEN** the original's labels SHALL remain unchanged (no shared references)\n159: \n160: ### Requirement: Build and test integrity\n161: \n162: The system SHALL compile cleanly and pass all unit tests for the CodeInterpreter types.\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: Package compiles\n165: - **GIVEN** Go toolchain and all dependencies are available\n166: - **WHEN** `go build ./pkg/apis/...` is executed\n167: - **THEN** the command SHALL exit with code 0 and produce no errors\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Unit tests pass\n170: - **GIVEN** the test file `codeinterpreter_types_test.go` exists\n171: - **WHEN** `go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...` is executed\n172: - **THEN** all tests SHALL pass, including enum constant tests, `TargetPort` tests, `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate` DeepCopy tests, `CodeInterpreter` DeepCopy tests, and `CodeInterpreterList` DeepCopy tests\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Generated code is up to date\n175: - **GIVEN** `make generate` has been run after type changes\n176: - **WHEN** `git diff --exit-code` is checked on `zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n177: - **THEN** there SHALL be no uncommitted changes (generated code matches source types)\n\n(End of file - total 177 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-002: CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义 — Delta Spec\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the Go type system for the `CodeInterpreter` Custom Resource Definition in API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, enabling declarative management of code execution sandbox environments with warm pool support and authentication mode configuration.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreter CRD type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `CodeInterpreter` as a namespaced Kubernetes custom resource with `Spec` and `Status` subfields, registered in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group.\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter type is a valid Kubernetes object\n- **GIVEN** the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` file exists\n- **WHEN** the Go compiler processes the package\n- **THEN** `CodeInterpreter` SHALL embed `metav1.TypeMeta` and `metav1.ObjectMeta`, and implement `runtime.Object` via `+k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object`\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter has status subresource enabled\n- **GIVEN** the `+kubebuilder:subresource:status` marker is present on the `CodeInterpreter` type\n- **WHEN** `controller-gen crd` generates the CRD YAML","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-002/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775875201663,"end":1775875201671}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875203032,"sessionID":"ses_285995f58ffe7A06Rb3mqAo6n0","part":{"id":"prt_d7a691b0300189A8u10nCbGJ2x","messageID":"msg_d7a690b07001zCO76DVAQWSq2I","sessionID":"ses_285995f58ffe7A06Rb3mqAo6n0","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_7bf5174c398d42db9c901de6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-003/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-003/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-003: CRD 共享类型与常量 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define shared types and constants in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` that are reused across AgentRuntime (AR-001) and CodeInterpreter (AR-002) CRD type definitions, establishing a single source of truth for port configuration, protocol enumeration, and authentication mode types.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: ProtocolType enumeration\n10: \n11: The system SHALL define `ProtocolType` as a typed string constant with values `HTTP` and `HTTPS`, serving as the protocol enumeration for sandbox port configuration.\n12: \n13: #### Scenario: ProtocolType constants have correct values\n14: - **GIVEN** the constants `ProtocolTypeHTTP` and `ProtocolTypeHTTPS` are defined\n15: - **WHEN** their values are inspected\n16: - **THEN** `ProtocolTypeHTTP` SHALL equal `\"HTTP\"` and `ProtocolTypeHTTPS` SHALL equal `\"HTTPS\"`\n17: \n18: #### Scenario: ProtocolType underlying type is string\n19: - **GIVEN** the `ProtocolType` type definition\n20: - **WHEN** the underlying type is inspected\n21: - **THEN** it SHALL be `string`, enabling JSON serialization without custom marshalers\n22: \n23: ### Requirement: AuthModeType enumeration\n24: \n25: The system SHALL define `AuthModeType` as a typed string constant with values `picod` and `none`, serving as the authentication mode enumeration for sandbox configuration.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: AuthModeType constants have correct values\n28: - **GIVEN** the constants `AuthModePicoD` and `AuthModeNone` are defined\n29: - **WHEN** their values are inspected\n30: - **THEN** `AuthModePicoD` SHALL equal `\"picod\"` and `AuthModeNone` SHALL equal `\"none\"`\n31: \n32: #### Scenario: AuthModeType underlying type is string\n33: - **GIVEN** the `AuthModeType` type definition\n34: - **WHEN** the underlying type is inspected\n35: - **THEN** it SHALL be `string`, enabling JSON serialization without custom marshalers\n36: \n37: ### Requirement: TargetPort struct\n38: \n39: The system SHALL define `TargetPort` as a struct with fields for URL path prefix (`PathPrefix`), port name (`Name`), port number (`Port`), and protocol (`Protocol`), with appropriate JSON tags for Kubernetes CRD serialization.\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: TargetPort serializes with correct JSON keys\n42: - **GIVEN** a `TargetPort` instance with all fields populated\n43: - **WHEN** the struct is serialized to JSON\n44: - **THEN** the output SHALL use camelCase keys: `pathPrefix`, `name`, `port`, `protocol`\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: TargetPort omits empty optional fields\n47: - **GIVEN** a `TargetPort` with only `Port` set to `8080`\n48: - **WHEN** the struct is serialized to JSON\n49: - **THEN** `pathPrefix`, `name`, and `protocol` SHALL be omitted from the output (omitempty behavior)\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: TargetPort Port field is required\n52: - **GIVEN** a `TargetPort` struct definition\n53: - **WHEN** the JSON tags are inspected\n54: - **THEN** `Port` SHALL NOT have `omitempty`, making it a required field in CRD validation\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: Single source of truth\n57: \n58: The system SHALL define `ProtocolType`, `AuthModeType`, and `TargetPort` exactly once in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`, with both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter types referencing these shared definitions rather than duplicating them.\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: No duplicate type definitions\n61: - **GIVEN** the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` package\n62: - **WHEN** the package is compiled\n63: - **THEN** there SHALL be exactly one definition each of `ProtocolType`, `AuthModeType`, and `TargetPort`\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime references shared types\n66: - **GIVEN** the `agent_type.go` file\n67: - **WHEN** the type definitions are inspected\n68: - **THEN** `AgentRuntimeSpec` SHALL reference the shared `TargetPort` type for its port configuration\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter references shared types\n71: - **GIVEN** the `codeinterpreter_types.go` file\n72: - **WHEN** the type definitions are inspected\n73: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreterSpec` SHALL reference the shared `TargetPort` type for its `Ports` field\n74: \n75: ### Requirement: DeepCopy generation for TargetPort\n76: \n77: The system SHALL generate `DeepCopy` and `DeepCopyInto` methods for `TargetPort` via `controller-gen object`, ensuring safe cross-goroutine value copying.\n78: \n79: #### Scenario: DeepCopy methods exist for TargetPort\n80: - **GIVEN** `make generate` has been run\n81: - **WHEN** `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` is inspected\n82: - **THEN** it SHALL contain `DeepCopyInto` and `DeepCopy` methods for `TargetPort`\n83: \n84: #### Scenario: DeepCopy produces independent copies\n85: - **GIVEN** a `TargetPort` with `Name` set to `\"web\"`\n86: - **WHEN** `DeepCopy()` is called and the copy's `Name` is modified\n87: - **THEN** the original's `Name` SHALL remain `\"web\"` (no shared references)\n88: \n89: ### Requirement: Build and test integrity\n90: \n91: The system SHALL compile cleanly and pass all unit tests for the shared types.\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Package compiles\n94: - **GIVEN** Go toolchain and all dependencies are available\n95: - **WHEN** `go build ./pkg/apis/...` is executed\n96: - **THEN** the command SHALL exit with code 0 and produce no errors\n97: \n98: #### Scenario: Unit tests pass\n99: - **GIVEN** the test files `codeinterpreter_types_test.go`, `agent_type_test.go`, `register_test.go`, and `groupversion_info_test.go` exist\n100: - **WHEN** `go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...` is executed\n101: - **THEN** all tests SHALL pass, including `ProtocolType` constant tests, `AuthModeType` constant tests, `TargetPort` zero-value/full-field tests, scheme registration tests, and GroupVersion constant tests\n102: \n103: ### Requirement: GroupVersion and SchemeBuilder\n104: \n105: The system SHALL define `GroupVersion` as `schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}`, a `SchemeBuilder` using `scheme.Builder`, and `AddToScheme` as the builder's add function.\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: GroupVersion has correct group and version\n108: - **GIVEN** the `GroupVersion` constant in `groupversion_info.go`\n109: - **WHEN** its fields are inspected\n110: - **THEN** `GroupVersion.Group` SHALL equal `\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"` and `GroupVersion.Version` SHALL equal `\"v1alpha1\"`\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: SchemeBuilder is configured with GroupVersion\n113: - **GIVEN** the `SchemeBuilder` variable\n114: - **WHEN** its GroupVersion is inspected\n115: - **THEN** it SHALL equal `GroupVersion`\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: AddToScheme delegates to SchemeBuilder\n118: - **GIVEN** the `AddToScheme` variable\n119: - **WHEN** it is compared to `SchemeBuilder.AddToScheme`\n120: - **THEN** they SHALL be the same function\n121: \n122: ### Requirement: Kind and GroupVersionKind constants\n123: \n124: The system SHALL define kind constants (`CodeInterpreterKind`, `CodeInterpreterListKind`, `AgentRuntimeKind`, `AgentRuntimeListKind`) and GroupVersionKind constants (`CodeInterpreterGroupVersionKind`, `CodeInterpreterGroupKind`, `AgentRuntimeGroupVersionKind`) in `register.go`.\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter kind constants are correct\n127: - **GIVEN** the constants in `register.go`\n128: - **WHEN** they are inspected\n129: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreterKind` SHALL equal `\"CodeInterpreter\"`, `CodeInterpreterListKind` SHALL equal `\"CodeInterpreterList\"`, and `CodeInterpreterGroupVersionKind` SHALL equal `GroupVersion.WithKind(\"CodeInterpreter\")`\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime kind constants are correct\n132: - **GIVEN** the constants in `register.go`\n133: - **WHEN** they are inspected\n134: - **THEN** `AgentRuntimeKind` SHALL equal `\"AgentRuntime\"`, `AgentRuntimeListKind` SHALL equal `\"AgentRuntimeList\"`, and `AgentRuntimeGroupVersionKind` SHALL equal `GroupVersion.WithKind(\"AgentRuntime\")`\n135: \n136: #### Scenario: SchemeGroupVersion aliases GroupVersion\n137: - **GIVEN** the `SchemeGroupVersion` variable in `register.go`\n138: - **WHEN** it is compared to `GroupVersion`\n139: - **THEN** they SHALL be equal\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Resource helper returns correct GroupVersionResource\n142: - **GIVEN** the `Resource(resource string)` helper function\n143: - **WHEN** called with `\"agentruntimes\"`\n144: - **THEN** it SHALL return `schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"agentruntimes\"}`\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: Resource helper works for codeinterpreters\n147: - **GIVEN** the `Resource(resource string)` helper function\n148: - **WHEN** called with `\"codeinterpreters\"`\n149: - **THEN** it SHALL return `schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"codeinterpreters\"}`\n\n(End of file - total 149 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-003: CRD 共享类型与常量 — Delta Spec\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine shared types and constants in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` that are reused across AgentRuntime (AR-001) and CodeInterpreter (AR-002) CRD type definitions, establishing a single source of truth for port configuration, protocol enumeration, and authentication mode types.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: ProtocolType enumeration\n\nThe system SHALL define `ProtocolType` as a typed string constant with values `HTTP` and `HTTPS`, serving as the protocol enumeration for sandbox port configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: ProtocolType constants have correct values\n- **GIVEN** the constants `ProtocolTypeHTTP` and `ProtocolTypeHTTPS` are defined\n- **WHEN** their values are inspected\n- **THEN** `ProtocolTypeHTTP` SHALL equal `\"HTTP\"` and `ProtocolTypeHTTPS` SHALL equal `\"HTTPS\"`\n\n#### Scenario: ProtocolType underlying type is string\n- **GIVEN** the `ProtocolType` type definition\n- **WHEN** the underlying type is inspected","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-003/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775875203024,"end":1775875203031}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775875203118,"sessionID":"ses_285995f58ffe7A06Rb3mqAo6n0","part":{"id":"prt_d7a692019001D7PnMY1DJe0gG1","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a690b07001zCO76DVAQWSq2I","sessionID":"ses_285995f58ffe7A06Rb3mqAo6n0","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":21851,"input":21653,"output":156,"reasoning":42,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.006303126}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775875204536,"sessionID":"ses_285995f58ffe7A06Rb3mqAo6n0","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6925b50017C9blLdHsMNErU","messageID":"msg_d7a692044001rmavPLVUvf7lqY","sessionID":"ses_285995f58ffe7A06Rb3mqAo6n0","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875206980,"sessionID":"ses_285995f58ffe7A06Rb3mqAo6n0","part":{"id":"prt_d7a692b26001v85QI2qW1ZCui2","messageID":"msg_d7a692044001rmavPLVUvf7lqY","sessionID":"ses_285995f58ffe7A06Rb3mqAo6n0","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_a6cf6cf2c76f472581350472","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/deployment/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/deployment/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deployment Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Deploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Helm chart installation\n9: The system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n12: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n13: - **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n14: - **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\n17: The system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n20: - **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values\n21: - **WHEN** pods for `workloadmanager` and `agentcube-router` start\n22: - **THEN** each container SHALL have environment variables `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` populated from those values\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Workload Manager deployment shape\n25: The system SHALL deploy Workload Manager as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `workloadmanager` with replica count, container image, service type/port, resource requests/limits, health probes, and optional `extraEnv` driven from `values.yaml`.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Default replica and service exposure\n28: - **GIVEN** default chart values\n29: - **WHEN** the chart is installed\n30: - **THEN** the Workload Manager `Deployment` SHALL use `workloadmanager.replicas` (default 1), expose HTTP on `workloadmanager.service.port` (default 8080), and use liveness/readiness HTTP GET `/health` on that port\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Router deployment shape\n33: The system SHALL deploy the Router as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `agentcube-router` with replica count, image, `ClusterIP` service mapping `port`→`targetPort`, resource requests/limits, optional dedicated `serviceAccountName`, and `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` pointing at the in-cluster Workload Manager service.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Router reaches Workload Manager by DNS\n36: - **GIVEN** release namespace `N` and Workload Manager service port `P` from values\n37: - **WHEN** the Router pod starts\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL have `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` set to `http://workloadmanager.N.svc.cluster.local:P` and container args including `--port=<targetPort>` and `--debug`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: Workload Manager ClusterRole permissions\n41: The system SHALL create a `ServiceAccount` `workloadmanager`, a `ClusterRole` `workloadmanager`, and `ClusterRoleBinding` `workloadmanager` granting the rules required for agent-sandbox, AgentCube runtime CRDs, core workloads, auth, and secrets.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Binding ties SA to cluster role\n44: - **GIVEN** chart installation in namespace `N`\n45: - **WHEN** RBAC resources are applied\n46: - **THEN** subject `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in namespace `N` SHALL be bound to `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` via `ClusterRoleBinding/workloadmanager`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Optional Router namespace Role\n49: The system SHALL optionally create namespace-scoped `ServiceAccount`, `Role`, and `RoleBinding` for the Router when `router.rbac.create` is true, granting secret management in that namespace.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: RBAC off by default\n52: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: false`\n53: - **WHEN** the chart renders templates\n54: - **THEN** Router optional RBAC manifests SHALL NOT be emitted\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: RBAC on with named service account\n57: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: true` and `router.serviceAccountName` set (or defaulted by template to `agentcube-router`)\n58: - **WHEN** the chart is applied\n59: - **THEN** Router pods MAY use that `serviceAccountName` and the Role SHALL allow verbs on `secrets` in the release namespace\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: Optional Volcano agent scheduler\n62: The system SHALL optionally deploy Volcano agent scheduler resources (ServiceAccount, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, Deployment) when `volcano.scheduler.enabled` is true.\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Scheduler disabled\n65: - **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (default)\n66: - **WHEN** templates render\n67: - **THEN** no Volcano scheduler objects SHALL be created\n68: \n69: ### Requirement: CRDs shipped with the chart\n70: The system SHALL ship `CustomResourceDefinition` manifests for `agentruntimes` and `codeinterpreters` under the chart `crds/` directory so Helm installs them with the chart lifecycle.\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: CRD group and scope\n73: - **GIVEN** chart path `manifests/charts/base`\n74: - **WHEN** CRD YAML is applied\n75: - **THEN** both CRDs SHALL use API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, and `scope: Namespaced`\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: Docker images for core binaries\n78: The system SHALL provide Dockerfiles to build three images: Workload Manager (`docker/Dockerfile`), Router (`docker/Dockerfile.router`), and picod (`docker/Dockerfile.picod`).\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Multi-stage Go build for control plane\n81: - **GIVEN** repository root as build context\n82: - **WHEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile` (or `Dockerfile.router`) runs\n83: - **THEN** the image SHALL compile the respective Go binary with `CGO_ENABLED=0` and run it from Alpine 3.19 as a non-root user (`apiserver` UID 1000 or `router` UID 1000) exposing port 8080\n84: \n85: ### Requirement: Makefile build targets\n86: The system SHALL expose Make targets to build binaries (`build`, related targets), run tests (`test`), build/push Docker images (`docker-*`), run code generation (`generate`, `gen-crd`, `gen-client`, `gen-all`, `gen-check`), and run E2E (`e2e`, `e2e-clean`).\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Default `make` builds workload manager\n89: - **GIVEN** Go toolchain and generated code prerequisites\n90: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make` (default `all` → `build`)\n91: - **THEN** `bin/workloadmanager` SHALL be produced from `./cmd/workload-manager` after `generate`\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: E2E entrypoint\n94: - **GIVEN** Kind, kubectl, Docker, Helm, and curl available\n95: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make e2e`\n96: - **THEN** the repository SHALL execute `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` which provisions the cluster (unless skipped), deploys dependencies, and runs Go and Python E2E tests\n\n(End of file - total 96 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deployment Specification\n\n## Purpose\nDeploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Helm chart installation\nThe system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n\n#### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n- **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n- **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n\n### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\nThe system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n\n#### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n- **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/deployment/spec.md","time":{"start":1775875206972,"end":1775875206978}}}}
