{"type":"text","timestamp":1775875264342,"sessionID":"ses_285995f58ffe7A06Rb3mqAo6n0","part":{"id":"prt_d7a695b500018E2SYNlsPduIG3","messageID":"msg_d7a6946a7001K496RT69Ej0QdU","sessionID":"ses_285995f58ffe7A06Rb3mqAo6n0","type":"text","text":"Now I have all the context. Let me write the delta-spec.md.","time":{"start":1775875264340,"end":1775875264340}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875264356,"sessionID":"ses_285995f58ffe7A06Rb3mqAo6n0","part":{"id":"prt_d7a695ccd001CMX3dfdlkk5f3X","messageID":"msg_d7a6946a7001K496RT69Ej0QdU","sessionID":"ses_285995f58ffe7A06Rb3mqAo6n0","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_5f75f516e5db4daf95cc0dc9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images) — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `docker`\n- **Language:** Dockerfile\n- **Size:** S\n- **Base specs:** `deployment/spec.md` (Requirement: Docker images for core binaries)\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Workload Manager Dockerfile (multi-stage)\n\nThe system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile` that builds the Workload Manager binary via a multi-stage Docker build: a Go builder stage compiles `cmd/workloadmanager` with `CGO_ENABLED=0`, and a minimal runtime stage copies the binary into an Alpine 3.19 image running as non-root user `apiserver` (UID 1000), exposing port 8080.\n\n#### Scenario: Builder stage uses Go toolchain\n- **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile` is invoked with the repository root as build context\n- **WHEN** the first (builder) stage is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL use a Go base image (e.g. `golang:1.25-alpine`) and set `CGO_ENABLED=0` in the build environment\n\n#### Scenario: Builder stage compiles workloadmanager binary\n- **GIVEN** the builder stage has the repository source available\n- **WHEN** `go build` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile `./cmd/workloadmanager` and produce a static Linux binary at `/workloadmanager` (or equivalent output path)\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime stage uses Alpine 3.19\n- **GIVEN** the second (runtime) stage in `docker/Dockerfile`\n- **WHEN** the base image is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL be `alpine:3.19` (or a digest-pinned equivalent)\n\n#### Scenario: Binary is copied from builder to runtime\n- **GIVEN** both stages exist in `docker/Dockerfile`\n- **WHEN** the `COPY --from=builder` instruction is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL copy the compiled `workloadmanager` binary from the builder stage into the runtime image\n\n#### Scenario: Non-root user apiserver is created\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n- **WHEN** the image is built\n- **THEN** it SHALL create a user `apiserver` with UID 1000 and set `USER apiserver` as the active user\n\n#### Scenario: Port 8080 is exposed\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n- **WHEN** the image metadata is inspected\n- **THEN** `EXPOSE 8080` SHALL be present\n\n#### Scenario: Entrypoint runs the workloadmanager binary\n- **GIVEN** a container launched from the built image\n- **WHEN** the container starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute the `workloadmanager` binary (via `ENTRYPOINT` or `CMD`)\n\n### Requirement: Router Dockerfile (multi-stage)\n\nThe system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile.router` that builds the Router binary via a multi-stage Docker build: a Go builder stage compiles `cmd/router` with `CGO_ENABLED=0`, and a minimal runtime stage copies the binary into an Alpine 3.19 image running as non-root user `router` (UID 1000), exposing port 8080.\n\n#### Scenario: Builder stage compiles router binary\n- **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.router` is invoked with the repository root as build context\n- **WHEN** the builder stage runs `go build`\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile `./cmd/router` with `CGO_ENABLED=0` and produce a static Linux binary\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime stage uses Alpine 3.19\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage in `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n- **WHEN** the base image is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL be `alpine:3.19` (or a digest-pinned equivalent)\n\n#### Scenario: Non-root user router is created\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n- **WHEN** the image is built\n- **THEN** it SHALL create a user `router` with UID 1000 and set `USER router` as the active user\n\n#### Scenario: Port 8080 is exposed\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n- **WHEN** the image metadata is inspected\n- **THEN** `EXPOSE 8080` SHALL be present\n\n#### Scenario: Entrypoint runs the router binary\n- **GIVEN** a container launched from the built image\n- **WHEN** the container starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute the `router` binary (via `ENTRYPOINT` or `CMD`)\n\n### Requirement: PicoD Dockerfile (multi-stage)\n\nThe system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile.picod` that builds the PicoD daemon binary via a multi-stage Docker build: a Go builder stage compiles `cmd/picod` with `CGO_ENABLED=0`, and a minimal runtime stage copies the binary into an Alpine 3.19 image running as a non-root user, suitable for execution inside sandbox pods.\n\n#### Scenario: Builder stage compiles picod binary\n- **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.picod` is invoked with the repository root as build context\n- **WHEN** the builder stage runs `go build`\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile `./cmd/picod` with `CGO_ENABLED=0` and produce a static Linux binary\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime stage uses Alpine 3.19\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage in `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n- **WHEN** the base image is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL be `alpine:3.19` (or a digest-pinned equivalent)\n\n#### Scenario: Non-root user is configured\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n- **WHEN** the image is built\n- **THEN** it SHALL create a non-root user (UID ≥ 1000) and set it as the active user via `USER`\n\n#### Scenario: Entrypoint runs the picod binary\n- **GIVEN** a container launched from the built image\n- **WHEN** the container starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute the `picod` binary (via `ENTRYPOINT` or `CMD`)\n\n### Requirement: Build context and reproducibility\n\nAll three Dockerfiles SHALL use the repository root as build context and produce deterministic, minimal images suitable for production deployment.\n\n#### Scenario: Build context includes Go module files\n- **GIVEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile .` is run from the repository root\n- **WHEN** the builder stage resolves dependencies\n- **THEN** `go.mod` and `go.sum` SHALL be available for `go mod download` before source code is copied (layer caching optimization)\n\n#### Scenario: No unnecessary files in runtime image\n- **GIVEN** a built image from any of the three Dockerfiles\n- **WHEN** the image filesystem is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL NOT contain Go source code, build caches, or the Go toolchain — only the compiled binary, Alpine base packages, and the non-root user home directory\n\n#### Scenario: Image builds succeed from clean checkout\n- **GIVEN** a clean clone of the repository at the correct commit\n- **WHEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile -t workloadmanager:test .` is executed\n- **THEN** the build SHALL complete with exit code 0 and produce a valid image\n\n### Requirement: Docker build output integrity\n\nEach built image SHALL contain a working binary that starts and responds to its health endpoint (where applicable).\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager image responds to /health\n- **GIVEN** a container running from the Workload Manager image with default configuration\n- **WHEN** an HTTP GET request is sent to `http://localhost:8080/health`\n- **THEN** the response SHALL return HTTP 200 OK\n\n#### Scenario: Router image starts without root privileges\n- **GIVEN** a container running from the Router image\n- **WHEN** the container's effective UID is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL be 1000 (the `router` user), not 0 (root)\n\n#### Scenario: PicoD image starts without root privileges\n- **GIVEN** a container running from the PicoD image\n- **WHEN** the container's effective UID is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL be ≥ 1000 (non-root user), not 0 (root)\n\n---\n\n## File Changes\n\n| Action | File | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| Create | `docker/Dockerfile` | Multi-stage build for Workload Manager (Go builder → Alpine 3.19, non-root `apiserver`) |\n| Create | `docker/Dockerfile.router` | Multi-stage build for Router (Go builder → Alpine 3.19, non-root `router`) |\n| Create | `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | Multi-stage build for PicoD daemon (Go builder → Alpine 3.19, non-root user) |\n| Create | `docker/.dockerignore` | Exclude `.git`, `test/`, `sdk-python/`, `docs/`, and other non-build artifacts from Docker context |\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775875264333,"end":1775875264353}}}}
